{{Fq
| width  = 350px
| source = ''[[Shami-Amourae]], former consort of Demogorgon''{{Cite dungeon/148/Wells of Darkness|80}}
| text   = Demogorgon is his own worst enemy. He is, in many ways, two creatures that share the same body. Aeumal, his left head, is the more charismatic and calculating while Hethradiah, his right head, is more impulsive and feral. Each views the other as inferior and each believes the other incapable of outfoxing itself.
}}

Each of Demogorgon's heads had its own name and personality, a duality that created an enduring internal conflict of his personality, while shaping all his actions and even his realm. His left head was named '''Aameul''' while the right was named '''Hethradiah''' (sometimes referred to as Hathradiah).{{Cite dragon/357/Demonomicon of Iggwilv: Demogorgon: Prince of Demons|20-32}}

Perhaps the only thing preventing Demogorgon from taking over the rest of the Abyss was his own dual nature.

{{quote
|If you want to have even a chance at stopping him, you need to distract him. That is Demogorgon's weakness. Each situation he faces brings two reactions, not one. And when faced with danger across multiple fronts, these reactions can paralyze him.
|''Shami-Amourae''
}}

Despite this internal madness, Demogorgon was extremely creative and relished experimentation and innovation.
